This paper deals with index reorganization, which is a common problem in database systems and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses optimization policies and rewrite rules, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper introduces a composable organizational grammar, which is related to programming languages and compilers, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category. Finally, the paper includes experimental analysis, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
